messages.message: Not sure where to post this, but it seems like I just lost write access to this shared folder (https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1O6EF9sepx7ImdrYJqSJyTSkmmxVnzWB-) in google drive. I was writing a doc that I created and exists in that folder, and all of a sudden it made me refresh, and I can no longer edit, but I can only make suggestions. Anyone else experience this issue?

Good catch, so it looks like we have some knock on effects from the @eng group being using some ways we weren’t expecting and some changes in Bamboo, we’ll get the perms fixed long term, but it should be back for you now.
Hm I still cannot change to editing mode
I think the updates might still be ongoing on the bamboo side, let me try one other thing
Can you give it about 3-4 minutes then refresh and try again?
I can edit it now, thanks!
:ty: for the call out, I deleted over in <#C0106JV0TFS|> since we chatted here and that shouldn’t be something others run into
